==English==

===Etymology===
From German ''[[Nixe]]'' feminine of ''[[Nix]]'', from Middle High German ''[[nickes]]'', from Old High German ''[[nihhus]]'' ‘water-elf, crocodile’, cognate with Old English ''[[nicor]]'' ‘water-elf, hippopotamus, walrus’ (English ''[[nicker]]'').

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/'nɪksi/}}

